commentPostTextItems.html: 10pm Looks like Imran Tahir is not coming out to bat, he has an injury, and Australia have won by 73 runs, series lead 2-1. Their bowlers started very well, both Hazlewood and Starc. Amla was fighting for South Africa with a hundred, they had a chance till de Villiers was there, but Australia prevailed once again. The next match is on Melbourne now, on Friday. Till then, goodbye and good luck!
Max: "South Africa manage to have the best no.5 in the world and still have a fragile middle order. Doesn't say much for AB's colleagues"
Sangit: "All wicket for seamer??? Is it so??" Absolutely!

Steven Smith is the Man of the Match: Finch laid the foundation early which was good for a big score. I had a pretty free reign to do whatever i wanted [about his flicks on the leg side]. We all practice hard in the nets for such shots and that's how we get better, that's how it comes out in the game. The boys bowled very well, in the right spots even after the ball got soft and it started to reverse. Hazlewood is outstanding these days and it's great to see Starcy back as well with some wickets.

commentTextItems.html: short ball outside off, he waits for it for the ramp shot but misses

commentPreTextItems.html: Omair Ali: "Steyn, what a fighting cricketer! Give him the ball or even the bat, he gives everything he has got. Bowled his heart while bowling, and now giving his best with the bat. Though, hard luck, SA!"

commentTextItems.html: slogged on the leg side for four! It was fullish on the leg side and Behardien smacked it wide of deep midwicket for four
inswinging low full toss just outside off, steered to deep cover for one
fuller and wider, pushed to point off the front foot
outside the off stump on length, Morkel swings and misses
inswinging yorker towards middle and leg, the bat comes down just in time to block and the ball misses the stumps by a whisker!

dismissalText.commentary: Dale Steyn c Marsh b Starc 12 (6b 1x4 1x6 6m) SR: 200

commentTextItems.html: taken at mid off, one more falls! Steyn had been targeting the region down the ground, he didn't connect that well and was caught by Marsh at mid off
shuffles across to the off side to scoop the ball behind square on leg and gets an inside edge on the pads. Umpire says it's a leg bye
full on the pads, driven down wide of long on in the gap for two. There's a direct hit at the bowler's end, it's gone to the third umpire and he's home easily
another one, no that goes all the way! Made room on the leg side, it was a straight delivery and he smacked it down the ground for a clean six
makes room again for the short delivery and slaps it down the ground over mid on for four
makes room to pull the short ball but sways out of the line
slightly full and wide, Steyn swings his arms to drive it to mid off
hops back in the crease for the incoming delivery and pushes it to mid on for one

commentPreTextItems.html: Ravindra: "This is the most disappointing thing about SA.. there top order increases the hopes of winning.. and sudden destruction.SA middle order is so fragile. Always makes there fans disappointed.. #disappointedfan"

bangs i the bouncer towards the leg side, not given a wide
makes some room and drives the full delivery down to mid off
low full toss well outside off, thick edge rolls down to third man for one
angled in this time and defends it back to Starc

stories.summary: Steven Smith has come in for high praise after his sparkling 73 in Canberra, with AB de Villiers dubbing him "a captain's nightmare", and Aaron Finch going one further by naming Smith in the same breath as de Villiers himself

stories.summary: Though South Africa lost to Australia in Canberra, AB de Villiers was able to take away a solid gameplan for the World Cup when they would play Ireland here: batting the opposition out
